    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>The Watson Park Church, also known as the Watson Park Congregational Church, was gathered
        in 1912 in the Dunning neighborhood of Chicago, Illinois. It was located at 6337 West
        Cornelia Avenue. The church joined with the United Church of Christ after the denomination's
        formation in 1957. The church dissolved around 2014 or 2015.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>This collection contains vital membership records for the Watson Park Church in Chicago,
        Illinois. The collection includes an early church register, membership records, baptismal
        records, marriage records, records of deaths and remembrances, programs for baptismal and
        wedding services, confirmation records, and a proposed constitution.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement>
      <head>Arrangement</head>
      <p>Materials in this collection have been arranged into chronological order by start date.
        Materials which are contiguous between folders have been grouped together.</p>
    </arrangement>
